    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-16T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="911"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/813: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-16T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 16, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1304. With further reference my 1295, December 15 and 1302, December 16. It is my
                    understanding that, if crew which brings Liberator back to Eskisehir wear
                    civilian clothing and carry American passports which have been duly visaed by
                    Turkish Consul, there should be no difficulty in arranging for their immediate
                    departure from Turkey.</p>
                <p>Captain Frederick Nesbitt and Captain Lyman Smith, two more of our interned
                    aviators who under instructions from Embassy have not given their parole,
                    escaped yesterday from their quarters in Ankara and are now on board the British
                    steamer <hi rend="italic">Gienbank</hi> which is about to sail from Iskenderun
                    for Port Said.</p>
                <p>Please inform General Arnold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
